Move more tests to run under content_shell temporarily

In these tests, text artifacts occur due to compositing of
antialiased contours and layer/compositing differences between
base and ref. These can be removed once headless WPT runner disables
antialiasing.

Slot invalidation for sibling-index()/sibling-count()

When the slot attribute changes for a shadow host child, other shadow
host children may have their sibling-*() function evaluation changed.

Note that changing the name attribute of slots does not require
invalidation as the elements slotted to the changed slot either all
starts being slotted there, or all stops being slotted. In both cases
the computed style is either all reset to nullptr or computed as a
result of the re-assignment.

Introduce RendererSideContentDecoding feature

This CL adds a feature flag, RendererSideContentDecoding and
chrome://flags/#renderer-side-content-decoding, to control whether
content decoding (e.g. gzip, brotli, zstd) is performed in the renderer
process or in the network service.

When the feature is enabled, the network service sends the compressed
HTTP response body to the renderer process, and the renderer process is
responsible for decoding the body.  When the feature is disabled, the
network service handles content decoding, and the renderer process
receives the decoded body.

Implementation details:

* In the network service:
  - This CL introduces a client_side_content_decoding_enabled flag in
    network::ResourceRequest. This flag is passed to net::URLRequest.
  - If this flag is enabled, URLRequestHttpJob will not perform the
    content decoding. It returns the original SourceStream. So the
    renderer process will receive the encoded body.
  - This CL also introduces a client_side_content_decoding_types array
    in URLResponseHead. This is filled by URLLoader::BuildResponseHead()
    when the client_side_content_decoding_enabled was enabled.
* For navigation requests:
  - In the browser process, when CreateResourceRequestForNavigation()
    method creates a network::ResourceRequest, the
    client_side_content_decoding_enabled is set to true if
    RendererSideContentDecoding feature is enabled.
  - In the renderer process, ContentDecodingInterceptor will intercept
    the response in RenderFrameImpl::CommitNavigation() to decode the
    body when client_side_content_decoding_types of the URLResponseHead
    is not empty.
* For subresource requests:
  - In the renderer process, when the feature is enabled,
    ResourceRequestSender sets the client_side_content_decoding_enabled
    flag, and insert a ContentDecodingURLLoaderThrottle to the beginning
    of the throttle chain to handle decoding the response before other
    throttles process it.
* For Service Worker Navigation Preload requests:
  - In the browser process, the client_side_content_decoding_enabled is
    set by the CreateResourceRequestForNavigation() method when the
    feature is enabled.
  - In the renderer process, NavigationPreloadRequest's
    OnReceiveResponse() method creates a ContentDecodingInterceptor when
    client_side_content_decoding_types of the URLResponseHead is
    not empty to decode the body.

Invalidation for sibling-count()/sibling-index()

1. Use the HasSiblingFunction() flag on computed style to tell the
   parent node that we have forward/backward positional rules.
   sibling-index() is forward positional and sibling-count() is both,
   but we don't separate between those functions during resolution.

2. Introduce a singleton TreeCountingInvalidationSet() that invalidates
   elements which have a ComputedStyle with HasSiblingFunction(). This
   set is scheduled for insertions/removals when the parent is marked
   as being affected by positional rules.

   An alternative would be to bake this into the
   NthSiblingInvalidationSet for the CSSGlobalRuleset. We could do
   that by unconditionally setting the invalidates_tree_counting_
   flag in the NthSiblingInvalidationSet. Alternatively we could
   detect the first time a tree counting function is applied, mark the
   CSSGlobalRuleset dirty and re-collect/create the
   NthSiblingInvalidationSet with invalidates_tree_counting_ set to
   true.

3. The invalidation required for slot assignment changes has not been
   implemented in this CL, but a couple of (failing) tests have been
   added.
